HEADWORD: Mixtion
<hw>Mix"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mixtio</ets>, <ets>mistio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>mixtion</ets>. See
<er>Mistion</er>, <er>Mix</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mixture.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cement made of mastic, amber, etc., used
as a mordant for gold leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mixtly</ent>⟦br⟧
